The family of Jephthah Yekorogha, has confirmed his release from the hands of his abductors on Monday.   A statement from Mr Austin Ekeinde, on behalf of the family, said Yekorogha has reunited with the family.   The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that no information was provided on whether or not ransom was paid before he regained freedom.   Yekorogha, a prominent politician and businessman in his 50s, was kidnapped at gunpoint, in front of his house at Biogbolo, Yenagoa by four gunmen and forced into their vehicle. A statement from the family disclosed that: “Our elder brother, Mr Jephthah Robert Yekorogha, was kidnapped at about 8.30pm on Monday, 24th January, 2022, in front of his house gate at Biogbolo, Yenagoa, Bayelsa State, by four gunmen in black uniform, who, at gun point, seized him in his car and forced him into their vehicle and zoomed off.   Ekeinde said that he is in good health, but would see his doctor for routine medical checkup.   “Once again, we appreciate all well-meaning Nigerians who by way of calls, text messages and visits stood by us throughout the ordeal.(NAN)